            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;As a measure of how seriously even WG14 (the ISO working group responsible for the C standard) take this, it is, so far, the ONLY feature formally removed from the C standard.  WG14 have a policy of &lt;i&gt;never break existing code&lt;/i&gt; (even if already fundamentally broken) - a policy they broke to get rid of &lt;code&gt;gets()&lt;/code&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;

