            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@supercat: the other problem with &lt;code&gt;fgets()&lt;/code&gt; is that if the file contains a null byte, you can&apos;t tell how much data there is after the null byte up to the end of line (or EOF).  &lt;code&gt;strlen()&lt;/code&gt; can only report up to the null byte in the data; after that, it is guesswork and therefore almost certainly wrong.&lt;/span&gt;

