            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Actually, the original C99 standard did not explicitly deprecate &lt;code&gt;gets()&lt;/code&gt; either in section 7.19.7.7 where it is defined or in section 7.26.9 Future library directions and the sub-section for &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;.  There isn&apos;t even a footnote on it being dangerous.  (Having said that, I see &quot;It&apos;s deprecated in ISO/IEC 9899:1999/Cor.3:2007(E))&quot; in the &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/a/19205993&quot;&gt;answer&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/users/1009479&quot;&gt;Yu Hao&lt;/a&gt;.)  But C11 did remove it from the standard  and not before time!&lt;/span&gt;

